.cs 3 on
.item 'SHOW VOLUME Command' 'Updated 1997/01/29 by MCL'
.itemix "'SHOW VOLUMES Command'"
.boxon
SHOW {VOLUME|VOLUMES} [collect-options]
.*                    <--------------->
.* FIELD COMMAND HELP SHOW VOLUME collect-options
.boxoff

.* DESCRIPTION
The SHOW VOLUME command displays the current volume that has been set.  Type
HELP SET VOLUME for a description of how to set a default volume.

THE SHOW VOLUMES command lists non-system-managed disk volumes that are
available.  The list does not include system-managed volumes, which constitute
most of the available storage.  In most cases you do not need to specify a
volume.

.* SELECT 'SHOW VOLUME Command Options'
.us Option Descriptions

.* OPTION COLLECT-OPTIONS,BY,KEEP,NOCLEAR,NOCLR,CLEAR,CLR,WARN,NOWARN
.optix collect-options
.ix collect-options 'on SHOW VOLUMES Command'
collect-options\allow you to insert the system response to the SHOW VOLUME or
                SHOW VOLUMES command into your active file.  Type HELP
                COLLECT-OPTIONS for a description of these options.
.cs 3 off
